			"updated_at": "2026-02-26T18:22:23Z",
			"body": "Thank you for the pull request! For correctness, this change looks good to me.\r\n\r\n> This is a problem because when you open a note in a new window and switch focus, WINDOW_FOCUS swaps the window states around — so state.notesParentType ends up pointing to the wrong window's value.\r\n\r\nA more in-depth explanation for how this fixes #14468 would be appreciated! How do incorrect values for `notesParentType` and `parentFolderIsReadOnly` break switching notes?  When the user switches back to the main window, `notesParentType`, `parentFolderIsReadOnly`, etc. should update to match the note list's content. In what cases are `notesParentType` and `parentFolderIsReadOnly` still incorrect such that #14468 can happen?\r\n\r\n(**Edit**: If this pull request is related to GSoC, please also [follow the GSoC pull request guidelines](https://github.com/joplin/gsoc/blob/master/pull_request_guidelines.md)).",
