			"updated_at": "2026-03-02T05:51:22Z",
			"body": "@laurent22 Yes, I'm completing this PR. I've added a test unit and updated the description with a detailed explanation.\r\n\r\n@personalizedrefrigerator Thanks for the review! Here's a more in-depth explanation:\r\n\r\n**How `WINDOW_FOCUS` breaks things:** When a secondary window gains focus, the reducer's [handleFocus](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/dhara/Documents/Aashish/vscode/joplin/packages/lib/reducer.ts:959:1-978:3) (reducer.ts ~line 960) **swaps** the WindowState properties — it copies the secondary window's properties into the top-level [state](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/dhara/Documents/Aashish/vscode/joplin/packages/lib/reducer.ts:455:0-460:1) and moves the main window's properties into `backgroundWindows`.\r\n\r\n**The bug:** Before this fix, `NoteList2`'s [mapStateToProps](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/dhara/Documents/Aashish/vscode/joplin/packages/app-desktop/gui/NoteList/NoteList2.tsx:328:0-355:2) was reading `notesParentType`, `highlightedWords`, and `parentFolderIsReadOnly` directly from `state.*` (top-level). Since each window has its own `NoteList2` instance, when the secondary window gained focus, the main window's NoteList would re-render with the **secondary window's** `notesParentType` and `selectedFolderId`.\r\n\r\nThis causes `parentFolderIsReadOnly` to be computed from the wrong folder (the secondary window's folder instead of the main window's). If this evaluates to `true` incorrectly, the drag-and-drop handler (`useDragAndDrop`) blocks interactions. Similarly, the wrong `notesParentType` can cause `useMoveNote` to behave incorrectly.\r\n\r\n**Why [windowStateById](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/dhara/Documents/Aashish/vscode/joplin/packages/lib/reducer.ts:415:1-423:2) fixes it:** `stateUtils.windowStateById(state, windowId)` returns [state](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/dhara/Documents/Aashish/vscode/joplin/packages/lib/reducer.ts:455:0-460:1) itself if it's the focused window, or `state.backgroundWindows[windowId]` otherwise. So each NoteList2 always reads its **own** window's state, regardless of which window is currently focused. This matches how `NoteEditor` already handles it.\r\n\r\nI've also added a test in the latest commit that verifies [windowStateById](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/dhara/Documents/Aashish/vscode/joplin/packages/lib/reducer.ts:415:1-423:2) returns correct per-window state after `WINDOW_FOCUS` swaps.\r\n",
			"author_association": "NONE",
