			"updated_at": "2026-03-02T17:04:32Z",
			"body": "Thank you for the additional explanation! I'm still not convinced that this change is related to https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/issues/14468.\r\n\r\n> This causes parentFolderIsReadOnly to be computed from the wrong folder (the secondary window's folder instead of the main window's). If this evaluates to true incorrectly, the drag-and-drop handler (useDragAndDrop) blocks interactions. Similarly, the wrong notesParentType can cause useMoveNote to behave incorrectly.\r\n\r\nLocally, even if I hardcode `parentFolderIsReadOnly` to `true`, I'm still able to switch between notes in the note viewer/editor pane (however drag-and-drop in the notes list doesn't work). As such, I don't think `parentFolderIsReadOnly` is related to https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/issues/14468.\r\n",
